==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[substantia]]'', '''substance''' or '''essence''', noun form from present participle ''[[substans]]'', from ''[[substare]]'', '''[[exist]]''', lit. '''stand under''', from ''[[stare]]'', '''[[stand]]'''

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-substance.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# Physical matter; material.
# The [[essential]] part of anything; the most vital part.
##that element of an object without which it would not exist
##the true meaning of something spoken or written
# Considerable wealth or resources.
#:''A man of '''substance'''.''
# drugs
#:'''''substance''' abuse''

